# PART 4 — Each Role's Day-to-Day Flow

### Tax Rules — Read-Only for Every Tenant Role (including `tenant_admin`)

**Updated:** a later backend push removed tax version create/activate/deactivate from
the tenant API entirely. `Permission.TAX_RULE_WRITE` no longer exists as a tenant
permission at all — tax law is now treated purely as jurisdiction-wide reference data,
owned exclusively by the platform team (see the Platform Admin section below).

**Frontend:** **Settings → Jurisdictions** (`/settings/jurisdictions`). On load it fires:
```
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tax/jurisdictions
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tax/rules
```
then, per rule returned, `GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tax/rules/:code/versions` to build a
jurisdiction → rule → version tree client-side (the backend doesn't return this nested
shape itself). Reachable by `tenant_admin`, `super_admin`, `payroll_officer`,
`finance_manager`, `auditor`, and `read_only` (whoever holds `tax_rule:read`) —
**not** `payroll_manager`, `hr_manager`, or `hr_officer`, who don't have that
permission at all.

The page lists each jurisdiction (country flag, currency, rule count). Click **Show
rules** to expand one and see its tax rules, and each rule's versions (e.g. "Nigeria
PIT 2026") with an effective date and an Active/Inactive badge — purely informational,
no buttons for anyone, tenant_admin included. A banner explains this is shared
reference data and to contact PayRole support for changes.

### Platform Admin — Tax Rule/Version Management

Creating tax rules and creating/activating/deactivating tax versions is now
`super_admin`-only at the **platform** level (`PlatformPermission.TAX_RULE_WRITE` —
`support_engineer`/`auditor` platform roles get read-only), via a separate controller:
```
GET    {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/jurisdictions
GET    {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/rules
GET    {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/versions?isActive=true|false
GET    {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/rules/:code/versions?isActive=true|false
GET    {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/versions/:code
POST   {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/rules
POST   {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/versions
PATCH  {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/versions/:code/activate
PATCH  {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/versions/:code/deactivate
```
**Frontend:** sidebar → **Tax Rules** (`/admin/tax`) — this page already exists and
already implements the full flow below (an earlier version of this doc claimed it
didn't; it does). Lists jurisdictions → rules → versions (same tree shape as the
tenant-facing read-only page), with **Create Rule**, **Create Version**, and an
Active/Inactive toggle per version, all firing the platform-write calls below:
```
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/tax/versions
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAccessToken}}
{
  "code": "NIGERIA_PIT_2027",
  "taxRuleCode": "NIGERIA_PIT",
  "name": "Nigeria PIT 2027",
  "effectiveDate": "2027-01-01",
  "basis": "annual",
  "bands": [
    { "sequence": 1, "lowerBoundMinor": 0, "upperBoundMinor": 30000000, "ratePercent": 7 },
    { "sequence": 2, "lowerBoundMinor": 30000001, "ratePercent": 11 }
  ],
  "reliefs": [
    { "code": "CRA", "name": "Consolidated Relief Allowance", "type": "greater_of_fixed_or_percentage", "value": 20 }
  ]
}
```
`GET /api/platform/tax/versions/:code` (and its tenant-facing counterpart,
`GET /api/v1/tax/versions/:code`) return a wrapped shape — `{ version, bands, reliefs }`,
not a flat version object — worth knowing if you're testing either directly in Postman.

### HR Manager (`hr_manager` / `hr_officer`)

Lands on `/dashboard` → HR Dashboard (headcount, new this month, missing-bank-detail
alerts, recent hires table).

**Add an employee:** sidebar → **Employees** (`/employees`) → **Add Employee** → the
5-step wizard (Personal → Employment → Compensation → Bank → Review). This route is
guarded — if you have zero legal entities yet, you get bounced back to Organisation.

Step-by-step API calls fired on final submit:
```
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/workers
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
{
  "employeeNumber": "ZL-0001",
  "firstName": "Chidi", "lastName": "Okeke",
  "email": "chidi@zenithlogistics.com", "phone": "+2348012345678",
  "dateOfBirth": "1992-04-15",
  "nationalId": "NIN-1234567890",
  "position": "Software Engineer", "department": "Engineering",
  "legalEntityId": "{{legalEntityId}}",
  "employmentType": "full_time",
  "hireDate": "2026-07-01",
  "bankName": "GTBank", "bankAccount": "0123456789"
}
```
(`nationalId`/`bankAccount` are sent plain — the backend encrypts them at rest and
never returns the decrypted value again; the UI always shows "Protected" after this.)

If you filled in the Compensation step too, a second call follows automatically:
```
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compensation
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
{ "workerId": "{{newWorkerId}}", "amountMinor": 50000000, "currency": "NGN", "effectiveDate": "2026-07-01" }
```
(`50000000` minor units = ₦500,000.00.)

**View/edit an employee:** click any row → `/employees/:id` → four tabs (Profile,
Assignments, Compensation, Payslips). Assignments tab is permanently empty — there's
no assignments endpoint on this backend at all, it's a known gap, not a bug you'll fix
by clicking around. Compensation tab is read-only history (`GET /v1/compensation/worker/:workerId`).
**Edit** button (top right) → `/employees/:id/edit` → fires `PATCH /v1/workers/:id`
with whatever changed (name/email/phone/DOB/national ID — no gender field exists on
this backend, and status changes are not available through this form).

**Give someone a raise:** Compensation tab → **Add Compensation** button → same
`POST /v1/compensation` call shown above. The new record supersedes the old one going
forward; the old one stays in history with an end date, nothing is overwritten.

**Assign an allowance/deduction to one person:** Pay Elements tab (on the employee
detail page) → **Assign Pay Element** → pick one of the tenant's pay elements (defined
under Payroll → Pay Elements), a calculation method (fixed amount / % of basic / % of
gross / formula), and an effective date.
```
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/workers/:workerId/pay-elements
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
{ "payElementId": "{{payElementId}}", "calculationMethod": "fixed", "amountMinor": 5000000, "effectiveDate": "2026-07-01" }
```
**Unassign** on that same tab soft-removes it (`PATCH .../pay-elements/:id/unassign`) —
it stops applying going forward but stays in history. **Edit** (next to Unassign) opens
the same modal pre-filled and fires `PATCH .../pay-elements/:id` instead — change the
amount/percentage/end date without unassigning and reassigning from scratch.

**Terminate an employee:** on the employee detail page (top right, next to Edit) —
**Terminate** button (hidden once the employee is already inactive). Asks for a
termination date and optional reason in a modal.
```
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/workers/:id/terminate
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
{ "terminationDate": "2026-08-31", "reason": "Resigned" }
```
Sets the worker's status to `inactive` — there's no separate `terminated` status on
this backend.

**Tax rules (read-only for you):** Settings → **Jurisdictions** (`/settings/jurisdictions`)
shows the same country/tax-rule/version tree as the Tenant Admin section above, but
without the Activate/Deactivate buttons — only `tenant_admin`/`super_admin` can flip a
tax version on or off.

### Payroll Manager (`payroll_manager` / `payroll_officer`)

**Set up pay elements first:** sidebar → **Pay Elements** (`/payroll/pay-elements`) →
**Add Element**. Give it a `code` (auto-uppercased, e.g. `TRANSPORT_ALLOWANCE`), a
name, a type (Earning / Deduction / Employer Contribution / Tax / Benefit), and either
a formula (e.g. `GROSS * 0.15`) or, if type is Tax, a tax rule code instead.
```
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/pay-elements
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
{ "code": "TRANSPORT_ALLOWANCE", "name": "Transport Allowance", "type": "earning", "formula": "GROSS * 0.15" }
```

**Create a pay run:** **Pay Runs** (`/payroll/runs`) → **New Run** → pick a Legal
Entity, name it, set period start/end and pay date.
```
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payroll/runs
{ "legalEntityId": "{{legalEntityId}}", "name": "July 2026 Payroll", "periodStart": "2026-07-01", "periodEnd": "2026-07-31", "payDate": "2026-07-31" }
```
Lands on `/payroll/runs/:id` in **draft**. Click **Calculate Payroll**:
```
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payroll/runs/:id/calculate
```
Page polls every 2 seconds while status is `calculating`/`processing`. Once
`calculated`, the employee register table appears (joined client-side from
`GET /v1/payroll/runs/:id/payslips` + a worker lookup per row, since the raw register
rows carry no name). Click **Submit for Review**:
```
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payroll/runs/:id/submit
```
Run moves to `pending_approval` (shown in the UI as "In Review"). You can also
**Cancel Run** from draft/calculated states — `PATCH .../cancel`.

**Approve or reject** — once a run is In Review, `payroll_manager` (also
`tenant_admin`/`super_admin`) sees the approval panel on `/payroll/runs/:id` — not
`finance_manager` (see the PART 1 gotcha above). **Approve Pay Run** now opens a
confirm dialog first (it used to fire immediately):
```
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payroll/runs/:id/approve
{}
```
**Reject** (labeled plainly now — it used to say "Return to Payroll", which read like
a distinct workflow step when it's the same `reject` call) requires a reason in a
modal:
```
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payroll/runs/:id/reject
{ "reason": "Missing overtime hours for Lagos branch" }
```
After approval, the run can also be **Reversed** later (with a reason) if something
was genuinely wrong — historical records are kept, corrections require a new run.
Reverse is `tenant_admin`/`super_admin` **only** — `PAYROLL_REVERSE` is never
explicitly granted to any other role in `roles.enum.ts` (not `payroll_manager`, not
`finance_manager`), it only reaches super_admin/tenant_admin implicitly through their
blanket permission grants.

### Finance Manager (`finance_manager`)

Lands on the Finance Dashboard (awaiting-approval count, cost-this-month, approval
queue). Click a queued run → `/payroll/runs/:id` — **fully read-only** on the payroll
run itself: no approve/reject, no reverse (neither permission is granted to this role
on the backend, see PART 1) — just a "Submitted for approval. Awaiting review." banner
while it's in that state.

**Disbursement (actually paying people):** sidebar → **Payments** (`/payments`) —
lists every approved-or-later pay run alongside its disbursement batch (or "Not
started" if none yet). Click **Initiate**:
```
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payroll/runs/:runId/disbursement
{ "executionPolicy": "manual" }
```
Depending on your tenant's approval workflow setting, the batch may need **Approve**
(`POST .../disbursement/:batchId/approve`) before **Execute**
(`POST .../disbursement/:batchId/execute`). Once transactions exist, a download button
streams the bulk bank file: `GET .../disbursement/:batchId/bulk-file?format=csv`. If
something fails partway, **Retry** re-attempts just the failed transactions.

**Tax rules (read-only):** sidebar → **Jurisdictions** (`/settings/jurisdictions`) —
same jurisdiction/rule/version tree as everyone else, no Activate/Deactivate buttons.

### Auditor / Read Only

Land on the default dashboard (HR Dashboard for auditor; a minimal dashboard for
read_only). Sidebar is limited to **Audit Logs** + **Jurisdictions** (auditor) or
read-only views of Employees/Pay Runs/**Jurisdictions** (read_only) — every write
button is hidden, and the backend would 403 anyway if one were clicked directly.

### Employee (`employee_self_service`)

Lands on **`/dashboard`**, which for this role is a small "Hello, {name}!" screen with
their latest payslip summary — built entirely from `GET /users/me` (name) and
`GET /v1/workers/:workerId/payslips` (payslip data), because this role has no access
to anything else. Quick links: **My Payslips** (`/my-payslips`, full history) and
**My Profile** (`/my-profile` — account email/name plus a **Change Password** form
using `PATCH /v1/users/me/password` with `currentPassword`/`newPassword`). There is no
"My Bank Details" page — this role cannot read or edit worker records at all,
including their own.

**`/my-profile` is no longer employee-only** — it used to 404/Access-Denied for every
other role (payroll/HR/finance/tenant_admin all got bounced), since it was hard-gated
to `employee_self_service` even though the page itself only ever called the universal
`GET/PATCH /users/me*` endpoints every role can already reach. Now every tenant role
reaches it from the same Topbar dropdown link, and platform admins reach it too — for
them it transparently calls `GET /platform/users/me` / `PATCH /platform/users/me/password`
instead, normalized into the same UI.

**Payslip PDF:** on `/payroll/runs/:runId/payslips/:payslipId` (reachable from My
Payslips → any row → View, or from a payroll run's Employee Register), **Download
PDF** now calls the real backend PDF generator (previously unused — the only option
was the browser's own Print dialog):
```
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payroll/runs/:runId/payslips/:payslipId/pdf
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
```
Returns `{ pdfUrl }` — generated on first call, cached (same URL returned) on
subsequent calls. **Print** (browser print-to-PDF of the on-screen page) is still
there separately, for a quick look without waiting on generation.

