# PART 5 — Password & Account Reality, Restated

- **Nobody resets their own password from a logged-out state.** There is no email-
  based recovery anywhere in this system.
- **Tenant admin-issued reset now exists in the UI.** Settings → Users & Roles → any
  active user → **Reset Password** button (tenant_admin/super_admin only, matches
  `Permission.USER_WRITE`). Confirms, then:
  ```
  PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/:id/reset-password
  Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
  ```
  Generates a random temp password server-side, returns it **once** in the response
  (`temporaryPassword`) — never emailed or stored — relay it to the user yourself. Also
  invalidates their refresh token, forcing re-login. This existed on the backend
  already but had no button anywhere in the frontend until now.
- **Still no equivalent for platform admins.** A locked-out platform admin (any
  `platformRole`) has no admin-issued reset path at all — only self-service
  `PATCH /platform/users/me/password`, which requires knowing your current password.
  Direct database access is the only recourse today.
- **Changing your own password while logged in** works for everyone, any role:
  `PATCH /v1/users/me/password` with `{ currentPassword, newPassword }` (tenant users,
  via `/my-profile`) or `PATCH /platform/users/me/password` (platform users, also via
  `/my-profile` now — see PART 4).
- **Nobody signs themselves up.** Every account — platform or tenant — is created by
  someone else calling a `POST .../users` endpoint with a password they chose.

